## Red Signal Sources (drives Sprint 3 2b implementation work)
- FIND-013 (route 2b) — Body VO type contract for ParsedNote.body
  - step2-scan-vault.test.ts:92  ERROR  Type 'true' is not assignable to type 'false'.  (predicate `_BodyIsBody`)
  - step2-scan-vault.test.ts:105 ERROR  Type 'true' is not assignable to type 'false'.  (predicate `_BodyTypeMatchesPort`)
  Why these fail compile: ParsedNote.body is currently `string`. With `Body = Brand<string, "Body">`,
  `string extends Body` evaluates to `false`, so the strengthened predicates `_BodyIsBody = false` and
  `_BodyTypeMatchesPort = false` reject `const x: false = true`. After 2b tightens stages.ts:32
  to `body: Body`, both predicates become `true` and compile passes. The cast at scan-vault.ts:127
  (`parsed.body as unknown as Body`) is the residual code-level work for 2b.

## Coverage-retrofit Tests (passing — codify sprint-2 routed findings the impl already satisfies)
- FIND-011 strengthened compile guards (step3-hydrate-feed.test.ts) — 3 type-level assertions
    1. `_hydrateFeedArity: _HydrateFeedSig['length'] = 1 as const`
       fails if hydrateFeed gains a second parameter (tuple length grows to 2).
    2. `_exactlyOneScannedVaultArg: _IsExactlyOneScannedVaultArg = true`
       where `_IsExactlyOneScannedVaultArg = _HydrateFeedSig extends [ScannedVault] ? true : false`.
       Tuple `extends` is length-sensitive: `[ScannedVault, Timestamp] extends [ScannedVault]` is `false`.
    3. `_noTimestampParamAnywhere: _IsNever<_NoTimestampParam> = true`
       where `_NoTimestampParam = Extract<_HydrateFeedSig[number], { epochMillis: number }>`.
       If any parameter is Timestamp-shaped, Extract is non-never and `_IsNever` is `false`.
  Replaced the tautological `const _noTimestamp: _NoTimestampParam = undefined as never` (FIND-011
  excerpt) which compiled regardless of whether `_NoTimestampParam` was `never`.

- FIND-012 strengthened compile guards (pipeline.test.ts) — 2 type-level assertions
    1. `_feedRestoredNeverPublic: _IsNever<_FeedRestoredNotPublic> = true`
       fails compile if `feed-restored` is added to `PublicDomainEvent` (Extract becomes non-never).
    2. `_tagInventoryBuiltNeverPublic: _IsNever<_TagInventoryBuiltNotPublic> = true`
       fails compile if `tag-inventory-built` is added to `PublicDomainEvent`.
  Replaced the tautological `const _f: _FeedRestoredNotPublic = undefined as never` and the analogous
  guard for tag-inventory-built (FIND-012 excerpt). Positive direction `_v: _VaultScannedIsPublic = ...`
  was already load-bearing and is preserved unchanged.

- FIND-014 / PROP-013 watchpoint runtime tests (pipeline.test.ts) — 2 new bun:test cases
    1. "FIND-014 / PROP-013 watchpoint: InitialUIState has EXACTLY {kind, feed, tagInventory,
       editingSessionState, corruptedFiles} — no Note aggregate retained"
       Asserts `Object.keys(state).sort() === ['corruptedFiles','editingSessionState','feed','kind','tagInventory']`.
       Under structural typing, a TypeScript shape constraint cannot prove non-retention; this is the
       load-bearing PROP-013 guard that the Phase 1c iteration-4 watchpoint demanded.
    2. "FIND-014 / REQ-010 NOTE: Note aggregate constructed by noteCreate is NOT retained on InitialUIState"
       Spies on `noteCreate` to capture the constructed Note (with a `__noteCreateSentinel__` marker),
       then verifies that no top-level `InitialUIState` value is the same reference and no value carries
       the sentinel marker. Sanity-checks that the noteCreate port WAS invoked (FIND-002 regression guard).

